      "evidence_quote": "This line reveals a mental trick: Jordan separates words from responsibility.",
      "rationale": "Goes beyond summary to analyze how a quotation supports characterization/theme; reasoning is solid and text-based, though not especially complex or multi-angled."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "T2",
      "level": "2",
      "score": 65,
      "evidence_quote": "Jordan insists, \"It was just a screen name, not a lie.\"",
      "rationale": "Uses some inquiry skills by selecting textual evidence, but evidence is limited (only a couple of quotes) and lacks MLA-style citation (author/page) required by the assignment."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "C1",
      "level": "4",
      "score": 85,
      "evidence_quote": "At the beginning, Jordan treats the fake name as harmless.",
      "rationale": "Paragraphs progress logically (beginning → progression → peak → resolution) with clear topic sentences and a strong concluding reflection; overall structure is coherent and easy to follow."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "C2",
      "level": "4",
      "score": 85,
      "evidence_quote": "The author does not present this as a perfect solution, but as a necessary first step.",
      "rationale": "Grammar, punctuation, and spelling are consistently correct with very few (if any) noticeable errors."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "C3",
      "level": "4",
      "score": 85,
      "evidence_quote": "The author uses this excuse to show how self-deception starts.",
      "rationale": "Uses precise, mature vocabulary (e.g., \"self-deception,\" \"persona,\" \"consequences\") that fits literary analysis and strengthens clarity."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "A1",
      "level": "3",
      "score": 75,
      "evidence_quote": "The online persona creates distance from real relationships because Jordan worries about being exposed.",
      "rationale": "Applies the theme to character behavior effectively (how identity choices affect relationships), though application stays mostly within familiar literary-analysis moves and could use more depth or varied evidence."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "A2",
      "level": "2",
      "score": 65,
      "evidence_quote": "Suddenly, the online space and school overlap.",
      "rationale": "Makes a basic connection between contexts inside the story (online vs. school), but offers limited broader connections (text-to-world/text-to-self) and does not connect to the assigned course text (*Ghost*)."
    }
  ],
  "notes": "Well-organized, clear literary analysis with effective quotations and explanation. However, it does not address the assigned novel (*Ghost*) and does not use MLA-style citations; broader connections are limited."
